  10:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** 
  11:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     EFI Hell to remap runtime address into the new virual address space 
  12:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     that was registered by the OS for RT calls.
  13:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** 
  14:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     So the code image needs to be relocated. All pointers need to be 
  15:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     manually fixed up since the address map changes. 
  16:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** 
  17:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     GOOD LUCK NOT HAVING BUGS IN YOUR CODE! PLEASE TEST A LOT. MAKE SURE
  18:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     EXIT BOOTSERVICES OVER WRITES ALL BOOTSERVICE MEMORY & DATA SPACES WHEN 
  19:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c ****     YOU TEST.
  20:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** 
  21:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** Revision History
  22:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** 
  23:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/runtime/vm.c **** --*/
